plt.ylabel('Region/Country/Area')
plt.title('Top 20 Region/Country/Area by Total Economic Values')
plt.show()

In [22]:
# Grouping by 'Region/Country/Area' and sum the 'Value'
grouped_region = df.groupby('Region/Country/Area')['Value'].sum().reset_index()

# Sorting the regions by total value in ascending order and select the bottom 5 regions
bottom_10_regions = grouped_region.sort_values(by='Value').head(10)

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(9, 5))
plt.barh(bottom_10_regions['Region/Country/Area'], bottom_10_regions['Value'], color='skyblue')
plt.xlabel('Total Value')
plt.ylabel('Region/Country/Area')
plt.title('Bottom 10 Regions by Total Value of Economic activities')
plt.grid(axis='x', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Analysis about the dataset

Two datasets were used for this analysis; one dataset is about Labour force participation and unemployment while the other is about Employment by economic activity. The datasets contains information across various regions, countries, or areas. It provides detailed statistics on different aspects of the labor force and employment by industry, broken down by gender. The dataset includes the following columns: Region/Country/Area, Year,Series and Value.

During the data preparation, I ensured there were no null values and also made sure all the columns had the appropriate datatypes. After that, I carried out the analysis and visualization of the dataset.
